pageContext.claim: “All of these states that are closed, North Carolina is closed -- these states that are closed are run by Democrats, and the reason they're closed is because we have an election on November 3, and they don't want the opening of the states and they don't want the income. They want to keep it nice and closed.”
pageContext.analysis: This is false. State rules on gatherings and social distancing are not determined by the election -- and, as it happens, coronavirus cases spiked to new levels at the time of the election.
